rComments: Tough class but one of my favourite professors. Knows a lot about the field and prepares you for writing your CPA exams. Take him if you like the more numerical approach because he likes detailed numbers and analysis but will reward you if you put in the effort.

Great enthusiastic prof. He made the material interesting an applicable.  Does a lot of case analysis in class too which is useful for the final exam. Teaches in a way that is easy to comprehend. He really enjoys it when students go to his office hours - he likes to get to know his students individually. Overall a great prof.

The course is hard, not the teachers. It's a hit or miss class where the class average is guaranteed a B- because of massive scaling (an announced guarantee). All you do is read/practice UFEs + group case, no final. Many people got A/B+s this year.

ok i had him in 426 and in 420. i actually enjoyed his classes and he tried his best. frankly he DOES know what he's talking about since he also teaches at the School of Accountancy! 426 was just a hard course that screws everyone over and i am no exception. in short: good prof, tough class.
